  geom_point()

There are so many different homeworldss in the key that the graph itself is tiny in the preview window extremely skinny! I would probably try to find a different way to present this data if it wasnt for an assignment.

  1. Make a boxplot of height.
ggplot(starwars, aes(,y = height)) + 
  geom_boxplot()

  1. Make a boxplot of height for each species present in the data.
ggplot(starwars, aes(height, species)) + 
  geom_boxplot()
## Warning: Removed 6 rows containing non-finite outside the scale range
## (`stat_boxplot()`).

5a. change the appearance of your graph in at least 3 ways.

ggplot(starwars, aes(height, species)) + 
  geom_boxplot() + 
  theme_minimal() + 
  theme(
    plot.background = element_rect(colour = "lightgray"),
    axis.title.x = element_text(color = "black", hjust = .5)) + 
  labs(
    x = "Height (cm)",
    title = "Starwars Characters Height and Species")
## Warning: Removed 6 rows containing non-finite outside the scale range
## (`stat_boxplot()`).

  1. Using any variables in the starwars dataset, create a graph that uses a color palette from viridis.
ggplot(starwars, aes(height, mass, color = species)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  scale_color_viridis_d(alpha = 0.5, option = "G") + 
  theme_minimal() + 
  labs(
    x = "Height (cm)",
    title = "Starwars Characters Height and Species",
    y = "Mass (kg)")
## Warning: Removed 31 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range
## (`geom_point()`).

7.Using any variables in the starwars dataset, create a graph that uses a color palette from RColorBrewer.

library(RColorBrewer)
ggplot(starwars, aes(height, mass, color = eye_color)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Pastel2") + 
  theme_classic() + 
  labs(title = "Height vs Mass Organized by Eye Color", 
       x = "Height (cm)", 
       y = "Mass (kg)")
## Warning in RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(n, pal): n too large, allowed maximum for palette Pastel2 is 8

  1. Using any variables in the starwars dataset, create a graph using facet_wrap
ggplot(starwars, aes(height, mass)) + 
  geom_point(color = "lightgreen") + 
  facet_wrap(~ species) + 
  theme_light() + 
  labs(title = "Height vs Mass by Species", 
       x = "Height (cm)", 
       y = "Mass (kg)")
## Warning: Removed 28 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range
## (`geom_point()`).
